article.headline: Iona 73, Niagara 55
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- Steve Burtt Jr. scored 15 of his 19 points in the first half to lead Iona to a 73-55 win over Niagara on Sunday. Charron Fisher led Niagara (3-9, 0-4 Metro Atlantic) with 14 points. Iona (9-3, 3-1) opened the game with a 17-1 run and led 33-18 with 6:30 left in the half. The Purple Eagles ended the first period with an 11-0 run and trailed 37-33 at halftime. Kiril Wachsmann, who came off the bench, scored 12 of Iona's 15 points during a second-half span, opening a 60-50 lead. Wachsmann finished with 14 points and eight rebounds. Marvin McCullough added 13 points and Ricky Solliver had 11 points and eight assists.
